  <div class="yui3-editable_text-text"><p>It might be useful to have a policy to control whether the copy-from functionality can be used or not, eg:</p>
<p>$ cat /etc/glance/<wbr />policy.<wbr />json<br />
{<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&quot;default&quot;: &quot;&quot;,<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&quot;manage_<wbr />image_cache&quot;<wbr />: &quot;role:admin&quot;,<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&quot;publicize_<wbr />image&quot;: &quot;role:admin&quot;,<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&quot;copy_from&quot;: &quot;role:admin&quot; &lt;&lt;&lt;<br />
}</p>
<p>this would allow an operator to enable/disable the copy-from functionality for regular users, and if desired, prevent data being copied from &#x27;external&#x27; sources.</p></div>
  </div>

  
